  <main>
    <div class="cover">
      <p class="eyebrow">Functional Requirements Document</p>
      <h1>Carty User App — QA Test Reference</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Covers every buyer/seller-facing screen in the Carty user mobile app: onboarding, wallet,
        creating and sharing payment links, scanning/pasting to pay, checkout, order tracking, and
        transaction history. Each module lists numbered, testable requirements with expected results —
        use the checkboxes to sign off a pass.
      </p>
      <div class="meta-row">
        <div class="meta-chip"><span class="k">Document date</span><span class="v">11 Jul 2026</span></div>
        <div class="meta-chip"><span class="k">App</span><span class="v">Carty user (mobile)</span></div>
        <div class="meta-chip"><span class="k">Platforms</span><span class="v">Android · iOS</span></div>
        <div class="meta-chip"><span class="k">Backend</span><span class="v">Shared Razz/Carty API</span></div>
        <div class="meta-chip"><span class="k">Status</span><span class="v">Ready for QA pass</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section class="module" id="setup">
      <div class="module-head"><h2>Test environment setup</h2></div>
      <p class="module-desc">What QA needs before testing can start.</p>

      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Detail</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><strong>API base URL</strong></td><td>Set in the app's <code>.env</code> as <code>BASE_URL</code>. On a physical device or emulator, this must be your test machine's LAN IP (e.g. <code>http://10.x.x.x:3005/api</code>), never <code>localhost</code> — <code>localhost</code> on a device resolves to the device itself, not the server.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Test accounts</strong></td><td>Register through the in-app Sign Up flow, or via <code>POST /auth/register</code> with header <code>X-App: carty-user</code>. You need <strong>two</strong> accounts to test payment flows — a seller cannot buy from their own link (rejected with "seller cannot buy from their own payment link").</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Email verification</strong></td><td>Creating a payment link requires a verified email (otherwise the API returns <em>"You must verify your email first."</em>). On dev/staging builds only (never production), the OTP screen accepts the override code <code>013579</code> in place of the emailed code.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Wallet funding</strong></td><td>New accounts start at ₦0.00. To test a <em>successful</em> payment end to end, the buyer's wallet needs a real credit — either a real transfer to their virtual account number (after identity verification), or an internal balance credit from an admin/staff account. Without funding, checkout will correctly hit the insufficient-balance path (see FR‑8.9).</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>QR scanning</strong></td><td>Requires a physical device with a working camera and camera permission granted. Simulators/emulators without a virtual camera feed will fall back to the "could not access camera" state, which is itself a valid thing to verify (FR‑7.4) but not a substitute for testing a real scan.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="module" id="regression">
      <div class="module-head"><h2>Regression focus for this cycle</h2></div>
      <p class="module-desc">
        These are freshly fixed issues from the current build. Give each one deliberate attention —
        they were either broken outright or silently wrong before this cycle.
      </p>

      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>
          <input type="checkbox" id="r1" />
          <div>
            <label class="item-title" for="r1">All displayed amounts show real naira values, not inflated 100×</label>
            <div class="item-note">Previously every screen that showed money (wallet balance, transactions, view links, link details, place order, order details, create-link success) displayed the raw kobo figure as if it were naira — e.g. a ₦15,000 item showed as ₦1,500,000. Check every money figure in the app against what was actually entered/charged.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <input type="checkbox" id="r2" />
          <div>
            <label class="item-title" for="r2">Scan / Paste no longer crashes</label>
            <div class="item-note">Previously threw "Could not find a generator for route RouteSettings('scanCode', null)" and hard-crashed the app. Confirm tapping the Scan/Paste quick action from the dashboard always opens the Receive Payment screen.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <input type="checkbox" id="r3" />
          <div>
            <label class="item-title" for="r3">Product image upload works and is optional</label>
            <div class="item-note">The "tap to add photos" zone was previously unresponsive, and Edit/Delete on an added photo did nothing. Confirm you can add, replace, and remove images, and can also submit a link with zero images.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <input type="checkbox" id="r4" />
          <div>
            <label class="item-title" for="r4">Insufficient balance shows a clear, specific message</label>
            <div class="item-note">Previously the app navigated to a fake "Order Placed Successfully!" screen even when the wallet debit failed. Confirm checkout with an underfunded wallet shows "Insufficient wallet balance. Please fund your wallet and try again." and leaves the checkout form intact.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <input type="checkbox" id="r5" />
          <div>
            <label class="item-title" for="r5">Freshly paid orders appear in My Orders and Track Order</label>
            <div class="item-note">A just-paid order sits in "in escrow" status until a rider is assigned. Previously it matched no tab in My Orders and never appeared in Track Order at all. Confirm a new order is visible immediately after a successful payment.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <input type="checkbox" id="r6" />
          <div>
            <label class="item-title" for="r6">Amount field doesn't freeze or crash while typing</label>
            <div class="item-note">The Total Order Amount field on Create Payment Link previously could throw a framework build-scope error while typing digits. Type a full amount (e.g. six digits) at normal typing speed and confirm the field stays responsive and formats live.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- 01 ONBOARDING -->
    <section class="module" id="m1">
      <div class="module-head"><span class="idx">01</span><h2>Onboarding</h2></div>
      <p class="module-desc">First-launch experience for a signed-out user, before any account exists.</p>

      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th class="id-col">ID</th><th>Requirement</th><th>Expected result</th><th>Pri</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑1.1</td><td class="req">App opens directly to the onboarding carousel on first launch (no session)</td><td class="expected">4 slides with animated background imagery, each with a headline and supporting copy; progress bar at top reflects current slide</td><td><span class="pill p2">P2</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑1.2</td><td class="req">Carousel auto-advances and can be swiped manually</td><td class="expected">Slides progress on their own after a few seconds; a manual swipe overrides and resets the timer</td><td><span class="pill p2">P2</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑1.3</td><td class="req">"Sign up" button</td><td class="expected">Navigates straight to the account-creation flow — no interstitial social-login picker</td><td><span class="pill p1">P1</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑1.4</td><td class="req">"Login" button</td><td class="expected">Navigates straight to the email/password login screen — no interstitial social-login picker</td><td><span class="pill p1">P1</span></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 02 AUTH -->
    <section class="module" id="m2">
      <div class="module-head"><span class="idx">02</span><h2>Sign up &amp; login</h2></div>
      <p class="module-desc">Account creation, email verification, login, and first-time PIN setup. Shared with Razz via the <code>techrific_auth</code> flow, scoped to Carty via the <code>X-App: carty-user</code> header.</p>

      <div class="field-list">
        <div class="field-card"><div class="name">first_name<span class="req-tag">REQUIRED</span></div><div class="rule">Free text</div></div>
        <div class="field-card"><div class="name">last_name<span class="req-tag">REQUIRED</span></div><div class="rule">Free text</div></div>
        <div class="field-card"><div class="name">tag (username)</div><div class="rule">Checked live for availability; auto-generated from email + last name if left blank</div></div>
        <div class="field-card"><div class="name">email<span class="req-tag">REQUIRED</span></div><div class="rule">Valid email format; must be unique</div></div>
        <div class="field-card"><div class="name">phone<span class="req-tag">REQUIRED</span></div><div class="rule">Must be unique</div></div>
        <div class="field-card"><div class="name">password<span class="req-tag">REQUIRED</span></div><div class="rule">Minimum length enforced server-side</div></div>
        <div class="field-card"><div class="name">referral_code</div><div class="rule">Optional</div></div>
        <div class="field-card"><div class="name">date_of_birth</div><div class="rule">Collected at sign-up; date picker</div></div>
      </div>

      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th class="id-col">ID</th><th>Requirement</th><th>Expected result</th><th>Pri</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑2.1</td><td class="req">Submitting sign-up with a duplicate email</td><td class="expected">Rejected with "Email is already taken", form stays filled</td><td><span class="pill p1">P1</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑2.2</td><td class="req">Submitting sign-up with a duplicate phone number</td><td class="expected">Rejected with "Phone is already taken"</td><td><span class="pill p1">P1</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑2.3</td><td class="req">Successful sign-up</td><td class="expected">Account is created and the user is logged in immediately (session token issued) — email verification is <em>not</em> a login gate, only a gate on creating payment links</td><td><span class="pill p0">P0</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑2.4</td><td class="req">Email OTP screen appears after sign-up</td><td class="expected">A 6-digit code is sent to the user's email; entering the correct code marks the email verified and shows a welcome message</td><td><span class="pill p1">P1</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑2.5</td><td class="req">Login with correct email/password</td><td class="expected">Session established, proceeds to PIN setup (first login) or straight to Dashboard (returning user)</td><td><span class="pill p0">P0</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑2.6</td><td class="req">Login with wrong password</td><td class="expected">Clear error shown, no navigation, password field not silently cleared without explanation</td><td><span class="pill p1">P1</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑2.7</td><td class="req">First login — "Create a PIN" screen</td><td class="expected">4-digit PIN entry, followed by a confirmation re-entry; PIN is required for future quick access / transaction authorization</td><td><span class="pill p1">P1</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑2.8</td><td class="req">Forgot Password flow</td><td class="expected">Requests a reset code by email, accepts the code, allows setting a new password, and that new password logs in successfully</td><td><span class="pill p2">P2</span></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
