    <!-- CROSS-CUTTING -->
    <section class="module" id="cross-cutting">
      <div class="module-head"><span class="idx">13</span><h2>Cross-cutting rules</h2></div>
      <p class="module-desc">Rules that apply across every screen above — check these opportunistically as you move through each module rather than as one separate pass.</p>

      <div class="table-wrap">
        <table>
          <thead><tr><th class="id-col">ID</th><th>Requirement</th><th>Expected result</th><th>Pri</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑13.1</td><td class="req">Currency formatting</td><td class="expected">Every money figure app-wide is a real naira value with a ₦ symbol, 2 decimal places, and thousands separators — never a raw integer, never off by a factor of 100</td><td><span class="pill p0">P0</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑13.2</td><td class="req">Error surfacing</td><td class="expected">Every failed action (network error, validation error, server rejection) shows exactly one toast with a specific, actionable message — never a silent failure, never a stacked duplicate toast</td><td><span class="pill p1">P1</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑13.3</td><td class="req">Loading states</td><td class="expected">Buttons that trigger a network call show a spinner and become non-interactive while in flight; they never appear to "do nothing" on tap</td><td><span class="pill p2">P2</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑13.4</td><td class="req">Empty states</td><td class="expected">Every list screen has a purpose-written empty state (icon + message) — never a blank area that looks broken</td><td><span class="pill p2">P2</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑13.5</td><td class="req">Back navigation</td><td class="expected">Every screen reachable from a quick action or list row can be backed out of without crashing or losing the previous screen's state</td><td><span class="pill p1">P1</span></td></tr>
            <tr><td class="id">FR‑13.6</td><td class="req">No app-breaking route errors</td><td class="expected">Every quick action, list row, and button navigates to a real, working screen — no "no route defined" crashes anywhere in the app</td><td><span class="pill p0">P0</span></td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- OUT OF SCOPE -->
    <section class="module" id="out-of-scope">
      <div class="module-head"><span class="idx">14</span><h2>Out of scope for this cycle</h2></div>

      <div class="callout limit">
        <p class="callout-title">Known limitations — do not file as bugs</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Direct deep linking.</strong> Opening a shared <code>carty.ng/pay/…</code> link outside the app does not automatically open the app to that order. Scan/Paste inside the app is the supported way to open someone else's link. Worth flagging separately if the business wants true deep links later.</li>
          <li><strong>Web browser access.</strong> The Carty user app targets Android and iOS only. It is not published for browser use — do not test it there for this cycle.</li>
          <li><strong>Rider-facing flows.</strong> Accepting deliveries, rider availability, and rider order management live in a separate Carty Rider app, not covered by this document.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
